      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(whatsapp): thread authDir through command authorization and owner bypass for LID JID resolution",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- WhatsApp group commands (`/new`, `/stop`) can be silently ignored when Baileys reports the sender as a LID JID (`@lid`) instead of a phone JID (`@s.whatsapp.net`)\n- Root cause: `resolveWhatsAppCommandAuthorized()` and `isOwnerSender()` called `getSelfIdentity()`/`getSenderIdentity()` without passing `authDir`, so the LID-to-phone reverse mapping could not happen and the sender was treated as unauthorized\n- Thread `account.authDir` through both command authorization and group owner-bypass identity resolution paths, enabling proper LID JID → phone E.164 resolution before owner/allowlist checks\n- Fixes #77755\n\n## Verification\n\n- `pnpm test extensions/whatsapp/src/inbound/access-control.test.ts` — 12/12 passed (including new regression test)\n- `pnpm test extensions/whatsapp/src/auto-reply/web-auto-reply-monitor.test.ts extensions/whatsapp/src/auto-reply/monitor/process-message.test.ts extensions/whatsapp/src/text-runtime.test.ts` — 58/58 passed, no regressions\n- Autoreview: clean — no findings\n- CI: pending\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: WhatsApp group commands (e.g. `/status`) from the configured owner are now properly authorized when Baileys reports the sender as a LID JID (`9876543210@lid`) instead of a phone JID, provided the auth directory contains a reverse mapping from the LID to the owner's phone number.\n\nReal environment tested: Linux x86_64, Node 22, branch `fix/issue-77755-whatsapp-lid-authdir` at commit `0b37c7e58c`\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n```bash\n# Build a temp auth dir with reverse LID mapping, simulate a LID sender,\n# and verify resolveWhatsAppCommandAuthorized returns true\npnpm test extensions/whatsapp/src/inbound/access-control.test.ts -- --reporter verbose -t \"authorizes group commands when owner sender is a LID JID with authDir\"\n```\n\nEvidence after fix:\n```\n ✓ |extension-whatsapp| ... > WhatsApp dmPolicy precedence > authorizes group commands when owner sender is a LID JID with authDir (issue #77755) 3ms\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: The new regression test passes: a group message from a LID JID sender with a reverse mapping in the authDir is correctly authorized as the configured owner. All existing 58 WhatsApp tests also pass without regression.\n\nWhat was not tested: Live WhatsApp transport scenario (no Baileys socket available in unit test environment). The repro is done at the source level with a synthetic auth directory and LID mapping file, matching the existing `text-runtime.test.ts` pattern for LID resolution tests.\n",
        "branch": "fix/issue-77755-whatsapp-lid-authdir",
